
[1]alp

   ALP, ALPS, n. [Gr. white; L. albus

   A high mountain. The name, it is supposed, was originally given to
   mountains whose tops were covered with snow, and hence appropriately
   applied to the mountains of Swisserland; so that by Alps is generally
   understood the latter mountains. But geographers apply the name to any
   high mountains.
